Female genitalia
(
Fig. 7
). Papillae anales sclerotized, covering dense spikes distally; posterior apophyses slen- der, almost reaching anterior margin of eighth segment; eighth sternite weakly sclerotized posteriorly, with paired hair tufts laterally at middle, anterior half sclerotized, waved on anterior margin; ostium bursae covered with dense micro spines, with sclerotized ventral margin; antrum funnel-shaped, as long as width of ostium bursae, densely covered with micro-spines on inner wall of posterior half, with anterior half smooth and almost membranous (
Fig. 8
); ductus bursae membranous and slender; corpus bursae elongated oval, membranous, signa two groups of some 15 spiked combs. Seventh sternite waved on posterior margin; seventh tergite rounded posteriorly (
Fig. 9
).

Biology
. Adult lay eggs besides the main vein on upper surface of the blade (
Fig. 13
). Larvae of earlier instars mine along veins and the black frass totally fill the mine during this time (
Figs 10, 11
). One or two mines per leaf. Larvae vacate the mine by chewing a circular hole on the upper side of the leaf (
Fig. 12
), then they feed exposed by making several irregular windows on the under surface of the same blade or other blades (
Figs 15, 16, 18
). The larva moults in a white flat cocoonet on the under surface (
Fig. 14
). The cocoon is white, having six to ten ridges on surface (
Figs 17
, 
21
). The pupa bears a small triangular cocoon cutter and the cremaster is comprised of one pair of teeth dorsally and one pair similar but smaller teeth laterally (
Fig. 20
).
